{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2510;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang3081\f0\fs22 "Xbox 360 Controller Emulator" allows your controller (gamepad, joystick, wheel, ...), function as "Xbox 360 Controller". For example, lets you play games such as "Grand Theft Auto" (GTA) or "Mafia II" using Logitech Wheel.\par
\par
\b System Requirements\par
\par
\pard{\pntext\f0 1.\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlbody\pnf0\pnindent0\pnstart1\pndec{\pntxta.}}
\fi-360\li720\b0     Only Windows XP SP3 and newer systems are supported.\par
{\pntext\f0 2.\tab}    .NET 3.5 (Also installs 2.0 and 3.5) (Included in Windows 7)\par
{\pntext\f0 3.\tab}    .NET 4.0 (link to 4.5, also installs 4.0) (Included with Windows 8)\par
{\pntext\f0 4.\tab}        .NET 4.5 is not supported on Windows XP SP3, download .NET 4.0 from here.\par
{\pntext\f0 5.\tab}    DirectX End-User Runtimes (June 2010) (Required regardless of OS)\par
{\pntext\f0 6.\tab}    Depending on the DLL, either or both of the following\par
\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1800 Visual C++ Redistributable for Visual Studio 2010 SP1 (Most titles use the x86 runtime whether your OS is 64bit or not) or\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Visual C++ Redistributable for Visual Studio 2012 Update 3 (Most titles use the x86 runtime whether your OS is 64bit or not)\par
\pard\par
Notes:\par
\par
\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720     Windows 7 includes .net 3.5 and its updates to .net 2.0 and 3.0\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}    For Windows XP and Vista, users can obtain it from the above link, and Windows 8 users can enable it in Programs and Features - Turn Windows Features on and off.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}    .Net MUST be installed prior to the DirectX webupdate as it checks that .Net 2.0/3.0/3.5 is installed and skips the Managed DirectX framework if it is not.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}    The full DirectX Redistributable will always install the file, however its best to have .net 3.5 installed anyhow as quite a few Xinput titles utilise .net for internal dependencies.\par
\pard\par
\b Introduction\par
\b0\par
"Xbox 360 Controller Emulator" files:\par
xinput1_3.dll (Library) - Wrapper library that translates the XInput calls to DirectInput calls, for support old, no XInput compatible GamePads.\par
x360ce.exe - (Application) - Allows edit and test Library settings.\par
x360ce.ini - (Configuration) - Contain Library settings (button, axis, slider maps).\par
x360ce.gdb - (Game Database) Includes required hookmasks for various games)\par
Dinput8.dll - (DirectInput 8 spoof/wrapping file to improve x360ce compatibility in rare cases - So only use if instructed to!)\par
\par
